reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great end table!
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for a narrow and tall end table for my bedroom that I could set my jewelry box on, since I haven't been able to find a jewelry armoire that I like. I love the open space of the cabinet and the one shelf is plenty to organize some overflow from my jewelry box. I build a lot of DIY furniture and this was pretty easy, just check the picture carefully because they have a lot of parts to go in on one picture. I could not tell from the pictures but it has a metal frame on either side! Very sturdy.I wouldn't recommend this if it gets a lot of use for two issues:- the drawer just slides on plastic runners and nothing to hold it in - sometimes feels like I'm going to pull it out- the black paint/coating is pretty thin and I chipped two places moving in into my roomThese issues don't bother me because I won't be accessing the drawer or door regularly, and a Sharpie easily covers chips (I have a dedicated Sharpie for all my black furniture!). Great value - I would buy another if needed, no hesitation.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 26, 2022
reviews.reviewText: It's really cute, small, but cute. I'm using it for a liquor cabinet and with the shelf I can't fit a handle of vodka. I ended up just taking the shelf out but I can add it back later if needed. The drawer is pretty big which is nice. I fit four shot glasses, a shaker, and some other little mixed drink tools and there's still plenty of room. The instructions were pretty self explanatory and easy to follow. There was little plastic pieces for the back I did not fully understand the purpose of but that could just be me. That was the only confusion during assembly. It's sturdy and the dark color looks awesome. Very happy with the purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 22, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Value for money
reviews.reviewText: Instructions were easy to follow and everything went together well except it was hard to get the screws into the holes to attach the top to the legs. It is a beautiful little cabinet and believe it will work well for the components for my TV.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 20, 2022
reviews.reviewText: SUPER EASY TO INSTALL!!! Seriously, I've put together my share of prefab furniture and this one was the absolute easiest...Of course, this time, I literally did follow the instructions :-) I was pleasantly surprised, even though it's prefab (pressboard), it is quite sturdy. Love the drawer and shelf inside. Way roomier than I thought. LOVE IT!I use it to put in cables and electronics (Wii) and a few games inside. Hides the ugly cables. Super value for the money too!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Finished product looks good
reviews.reviewText: The diagrams made it easy to assemble. I liked how every part was labeled including all the little bits of hardware. I liked the reinforcements, the tab to keep the drawer from coming all the way out.It took me (over 70 yrs. old) 1 3/4 hours to assemble and I was working slowly.I bought this cabinet as it was the perfect size to put next to my ironing board. It holds pressing tools, extra iron, pressing cloths, etc.I didn't want a cabinet that looked like it belonged in a laundry room or bathroom and this cabinet is working out perfectly. The height of the cabinet is approximately the same height as my ironing board so it gives me a place to temporarily place scissors, pins, etc. while sewing/pressing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute cabinets with great price!
reviews.reviewText: I bought 2 cabinets to go in our new 4 Season's Room. Love the way they look with our Mango Wood Table and grey walls. The first one was a little tricky to put together because we are not good at this. However I put the second one together by myself easily after I knew how to do it. The price was great for the product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and easy to assemble.
reviews.reviewText: Perfect size for a corner of my bathroom.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Will do the Job
reviews.reviewText: Now I know why this one was $89.00 and the good ones ran about $300 or so. Directions were at times difficult to understand, but manageable. Nice small size is just what I needed. One large side piece arrived slightly bent and thus cracked. Not worth returning. I'm using it that way. Everything fit together well. Does the job, but I got a lock for it and now I'm laughing my head off over it. Not installing it. Good enough for light duty.
